{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"35edc45a-9326-462e-b24e-370b77ff2497","content":"In .NET MAUI, you configure platform lifecycle events in your `MauiProgram.cs` using `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* runs on pause */ })\n        .OnStop(activity => { /* runs on stop */ }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* runs on background */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;`\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code separated\n- The delegates receive the native platform object (`Activity` on Android, `UIApplication` on iOS)\n- Other available Android events: `OnCreate`, `OnResume`, `OnDestroy`, `OnRestart`\n- Other available iOS events: `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate`, `OnActivated`, `OnResignActivation`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1bee6cfc-b401-4413-a1f9-be5b41c06663","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI - specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":363,"requestId":"5013:739A4:1B87D99:1E8F282:69FA9080"},"id":"34429d55-82a4-4c47-8faf-e9e1b26e40f0","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:51:19.353Z","parentId":"c6cb2454-d00f-4e73-a751-b25dc9109f69"}
